trans-unit.source: Transports and Message Formats Supported for a Bridge
trans-unit.target: Transports and Message Formats Supported for a Bridge

trans-unit.source: This topic lists the message formats currently supported by <token>af_integration</token> bridges.
trans-unit.target: This topic lists the message formats currently supported by <token>af_integration</token> bridges.

trans-unit.source: For the current release, the <token>xml_bridge</token> supports processing the following message formats:
trans-unit.target: For the current release, the <token>xml_bridge</token> supports processing the following message formats:

trans-unit.source: SOAP messages over HTTP, FTP, or SFTP.
trans-unit.target: SOAP messages over HTTP, FTP, or SFTP.

trans-unit.source: POX (Plain Old XML) messages over HTTP, FTP, or SFTP.
trans-unit.target: POX (Plain Old XML) messages over HTTP, FTP, or SFTP.

trans-unit.source: Flat files over HTTP, FTP, or SFTP.
trans-unit.target: Flat files over HTTP, FTP, or SFTP.

trans-unit.source: Flat file support is available only for <token>one-way</token>.
trans-unit.target: Flat file support is available only for <token>one-way</token>.
